<font color="#FF0000">MAYA'S FORTITUDE AND VISION</font><br>
<tt>Tue Dec  3 16:42:58 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I am thankful for the work Maya Lin has done to memorialize the Vietnam War and    Civil Rights Movement.  Her strength against obvious racial and gender bias (and outright hatred toward her work) has been tested throughout her still young career, yet her clear strong vision of artistic form and function remains.  Ms. Lin's stand during the Vietnam War Memorial's debate further demonstrates that art and politics do not easily mix, and dialog and time can often resolve matters better than rash stereotyping and decision-making of new visions of artistic design.  I forward to Maya Lin my appreciation for all she's done and best wishes for all she's yet to do.
<p><code>-- DSchleg@emich.emuvax  (David C. Schleg) </code><p>


